And that was bad.

00:04:01.420 --> 00:04:02.594
Not deliberate.

00:04:02.618 --> 00:04:04.622
BG: It's funny,
it's hard to remember that,

00:04:04.646 --> 00:04:07.694
but there was a period
where Apple users felt

00:04:07.718 --> 00:04:10.796
maybe they were in opposition
or something like that.

00:04:10.820 --> 00:04:12.488
CA: Yeah, it was intense,

00:04:12.512 --> 00:04:17.375
the bad feelings in different sections
of the technology world were amazing.

00:04:17.844 --> 00:04:19.535
I'm excited for this conversation,

00:04:19.559 --> 00:04:22.903
because you have shape-shifted the world
in so many different ways.

00:04:22.927 --> 00:04:25.442
And there's three in particular
I'd love us to cover.

00:04:25.466 --> 00:04:28.950
There's what you did
as a technologist through Microsoft,

00:04:28.974 --> 00:04:30.942
what you've done as a philanthropist,